    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Pedestrians vs. Scooter</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Carol Saul letter welcomes Segway personal scooters as alternative to polluting vehicles and suggests they share bicycle lanes (Jan 23 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''On the Pavement, a New Contender'' (Jan. 23): I would welcome Segways only as an alternative to polluting vehicles like cars or motorcycles. Let its proponents share bicycle lanes with in-line skaters.</p>
        <p>CAROL SAUL  New York</p>
      </block>
